==English==
===Etymology ===
From German: ''[[Fest]]'', festival and ''[[Schrift]]'', writing, from Middle High German ''Schrift'', from Old High German ''Scrift'', from ''scrban'', to write, from Latin ''scrbere'', from an Indo-European Root believed to be ''skrbh-''. 

=== Noun===
'''festschrift''' (plural '''festschrifts''', '''festschriften''' )

# A [[tribute]] or [[memorial]] volume filled with [[essay]]s and [[article]]s by [[admirer]]s in memory of a dead [[colleague]].
